Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.17,0:00:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,JAHRESZEIT HOTEL\N(FRANKFURT)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.98,0:00:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The experiments…\Nof the Red Rose Mansion are…
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.77,0:00:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,still happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.90,0:00:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And that devil…\Nhe's got himself an apprentice now.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.65,0:00:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy with glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.11,0:00:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The survivor of… the Red Rose Mansion…
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.87,0:00:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Petr Čapek.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.71,0:00:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That guy…\Nhe's trying to control the devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.91,0:01:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Follow that car.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.63,0:01:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He's getting away!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.43,0:03:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Where…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.93,0:03:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.56,0:03:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you conscious now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.57,0:03:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.73,0:03:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.11,0:03:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You're lucky.\NAll you got was a sprained ankle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.82,0:04:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I checked your head,\Nbut I don't think you hit it hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.29,0:04:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm not a specialist like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.33,0:04:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.58,0:04:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Dr. Tenma, the gifted neurosurgeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.84,0:04:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I read about you in the paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.50,0:04:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.92,0:04:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a dentist around here.\NI'm Milan Kolasch.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.47,0:04:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I just happened to pass by\Nafter you were hit by that car.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.89,0:04:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The driver got the heck out of there fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.39,0:04:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You should stay in bed some more.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.48,0:04:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I'll only cause you trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.56,0:04:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Letting you walk out of here on that leg
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.98,0:04:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and getting snatched by the cops\Naround here would be even bigger trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.07,0:04:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.16,0:04:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Turkish Quarter of Frankfurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.70,0:04:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The Turkish Quarter?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.45,0:04:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more like\Nthis used to be the Turkish Quarter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.63,0:04:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They're tearing down everything\Nin the name of redevelopment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.09,0:04:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Nearly all the Turks\Naround here have moved elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.18,0:05:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Before, when the right-wing extremists\Ntried to burn this place down,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.05,0:05:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we banded together to fight them off.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.22,0:05:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the Bahir Cafe also gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.94,0:05:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It disappeared long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.81,0:05:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know this neighborhood?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.40,0:05:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.03,0:05:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, if you can stand,\Nwhy not eat with us there?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.20,0:05:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Food's better when it's shared.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.74,0:05:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, it's Vietnamese food.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.62,0:05:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Minh made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.41,0:05:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There's pho ga and cha gio tom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.25,0:05:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Minh's Vietnamese dishes are the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.01,0:05:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Help yourself to all you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.43,0:05:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.35,0:05:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I love pork,\Nbut the Turks' religion forbids eating it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.94,0:05:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't get much Czech food.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.90,0:05:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because Milan is a terrible cook.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.86,0:06:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.28,0:06:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone takes turns\Nmaking dishes from their own country.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.57,0:06:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a luxury being able to enjoy food\Nfrom different countries every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.29,0:06:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Japanese, right, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.45,0:06:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of Japanese food is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.79,0:06:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Japanese food?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.58,0:06:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I know!\NWhy don't you cook us some next time?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.30,0:06:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hardly wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.59,0:06:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see. There's pork in katsudon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.26,0:06:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And sushi…\NSome people don't like raw fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.31,0:06:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,How about oyakodon?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.35,0:06:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oyakodon?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.77,0:06:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It's rice topped with chicken\Nand eggs mixed with a sauce.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.44,0:06:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Why's it called oyakodon?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.61,0:06:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oya is "parent," and ko is "child."\NDon means "bowl."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.28,0:06:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's "parent and child bowl"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.53,0:06:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Japanese cooking sure has\Na funny sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.37,0:06:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The chicken and egg\Nare the parent and child!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.91,0:06:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.63,0:06:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.34,0:07:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you like the food?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.05,0:07:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,No. It's delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.93,0:07:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been such a long time
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.51,0:07:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,since I had such good food…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.77,0:07:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and such a pleasant meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.61,0:07:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night, Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.32,0:07:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.41,0:07:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder how long it will take\Nbefore I can walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.50,0:07:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have time to lie around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.43,0:07:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Petr… Čapek…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.27,0:08:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.11,0:08:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,A report on Petr Čapek's movements.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.20,0:08:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It must have seemed strange to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.87,0:08:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The cops showed up so quickly\Nnot because they were after you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.37,0:08:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The cops were watching him\Nto protect him from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.13,0:08:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to kill Petr Čapek.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.85,0:08:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.64,0:08:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.48,0:08:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to be able to make ones\Nthat flew far.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.90,0:08:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Milan's good at making paper airplanes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.77,0:08:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They fly all the way\Nover those roofs over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.11,0:08:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.61,0:08:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what Milan always says?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.57,0:08:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He made us a promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.91,0:08:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to go even farther\Nthan just those roofs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.71,0:09:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go to Turkey and Vietnam,\Nand even the Czech Republic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.42,0:09:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll visit all our countries together.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.92,0:09:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,-Right?\N-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.59,0:09:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Fly!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.47,0:09:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.85,0:09:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,-Why won't it fly?\N-I wonder why.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.64,0:09:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to kill Petr Čapek.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.02,0:09:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you going to do that, Milan?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.65,0:09:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That guy… That Petr Čapek is…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.41,0:09:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,a devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.08,0:09:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1989, the night before
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.45,0:09:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the collapse of the\NCzechoslovakia Communist Party,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.96,0:09:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,he escaped to this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.29,0:09:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,After he moved here to Frankfurt,\Nhe started a school teaching German.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.88,0:09:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a very quiet man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.05,0:09:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But after a while,\Na change came over the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.77,0:10:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The children from his school\Nstarted killing themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.61,0:10:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they started\Nto become extremely violent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.19,0:10:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Then one day, there was a riot
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.36,0:10:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that was nothing less than\Nchild-on-child murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.87,0:10:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I interviewed the child who was the leader\Nof the incident when he was in custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.46,0:10:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what he told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.79,0:10:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,"I want to go back to the book readings."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.42,0:10:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Book readings?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.76,0:10:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That night, while in custody,\Nthe boy killed himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.81,0:10:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He was my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.35,0:10:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In the uproar,\NČapek left the city and disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.90,0:10:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The next time he showed up here,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.86,0:10:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,he was like a different person.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.53,0:10:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He led\Na Frankfurt underground organization
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.78,0:10:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and had joined forces\Nwith right-wing extremists.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.28,0:11:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he began to drive out Turks\Nand other foreigners from the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.46,0:11:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know\Nwhat he's trying to do with this city.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.21,0:11:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But their violence reached its peak
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.92,0:11:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,when they tried to burn down\Nthe Turkish Quarter in 1996.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.14,0:11:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You know about that incident, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.01,0:11:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I saw it on the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.64,0:11:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The people in this neighborhood formed\Na vigilante group to resist them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.36,0:11:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But in a mere three months,\Nthe five leaders
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.82,0:11:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of the vigilante group
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.36,0:11:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,died one by one in unexplained incidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.53,0:11:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And those five dead people are…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.83,0:11:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Suleiman's son, Tung's father,\NMinh's husband,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.79,0:11:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Mustafa's son, and Shemel's father.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.17,0:11:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't just die.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.84,0:11:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They were murdered…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.93,0:11:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,by Petr Čapek.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.31,0:12:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why you were watching Čapek.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.56,0:12:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'll tell you one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.56,0:12:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I will be the person who kills Čapek.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.53,0:12:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Just you watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.78,0:12:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I think this next one will do well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.91,0:12:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.95,0:12:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I worked hard on this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.08,0:12:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how hard you try,\Nsome things are just impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.08,0:12:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We already know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.00,0:12:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that all of us traveling\Nto Turkey or Vietnam is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.88,0:12:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just fine living here
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.76,0:12:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,with Milan and Tung.\NI don't need to go on any trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.80,0:12:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.31,0:12:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, it's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.77,0:12:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This one will fly for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.90,0:12:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.07,0:12:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.49,0:12:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You did it! It's flying!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.07,0:12:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing! Look at it go!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.32,0:13:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure I can get it\Nto fly over the roofs like Milan's.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.03,0:13:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But I still got it to fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.29,0:13:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you glad we didn't give up?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.12,0:13:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yes!\N-Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.33,0:13:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't ever give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.40,0:13:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's my gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.24,0:13:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you do with my gun\Nthat was in that drawer?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.29,0:13:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,My chance to shoot Čapek is here.\NI'm going now to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.29,0:13:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me back my gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.92,0:13:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't let you do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.88,0:14:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't give you your gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.84,0:14:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the gun that was in your coat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.01,0:14:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,When I do this, I want to use\Nthe gun I've trained with.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.02,0:14:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, will you give me my gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.64,0:14:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a family now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.40,0:14:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.52,0:14:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been watching Čapek's movements\Nfor a very long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.40,0:14:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no better chance\Nto kill him than today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.82,0:14:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.74,0:14:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do this, Milan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.12,0:14:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't I make myself clear?\NDon't interfere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.58,0:14:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you get vengeance now,\Nthe dead won't come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.54,0:14:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What's more, think about the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.30,0:14:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You have no right to talk to me like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.72,0:14:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Milan…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.68,0:14:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You and I are the same, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.52,0:14:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked into you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.23,0:14:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If what you claim is true,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.36,0:15:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,what you and I are\Ntrying to do is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.69,0:15:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't use to be that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.53,0:15:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The Čapek I knew…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.53,0:15:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,wasn't the devil he's become!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.12,0:15:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Petr Čapek and I were childhood friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.25,0:15:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the one\Nwho invited him to this country!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.34,0:15:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think\Nis on the other side of the border?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.80,0:15:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not supposed to go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.34,0:15:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I know we're not supposed to go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.39,0:15:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But haven't you heard?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.72,0:15:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a wonderful place\Non the other side of the border.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.94,0:15:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They have cities\Nthat are lit up all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.44,0:15:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure, Petr? Who told you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.02,0:15:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Old Man Gregor did.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.44,0:15:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That guy's an alcoholic.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.45,0:15:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, I've heard there is something
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.49,0:15:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,across the border that ruins people,\Nlike how Old Man Gregor is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.78,0:15:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Something that ruins people, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.41,0:15:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.29,0:15:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would you want to see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.00,0:15:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Fly!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.59,0:16:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's caught the wind!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.75,0:16:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You're good, Milan!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.01,0:16:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at it fly!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.26,0:16:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! That one's going to cross the border!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.93,0:16:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Go take a look for us!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.43,0:16:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We grew up in a town\Nnear the Czechoslovakia-Austrian border.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.06,0:16:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Mine was a blue-collar family,\Nhis was a white-collar one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.23,0:16:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But for some strange reason,\Nwe got along together.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.44,0:16:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1989, when the Czechoslovakia\NCommunist Party collapsed,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.99,0:16:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I was the one who helped him defect.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.75,0:16:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The one\Nwho invited that devil to this country…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.25,0:16:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.25,0:16:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,PRAGUE,1969
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.68,0:16:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I was worried about you\Nwhen the Soviet Army invaded last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.48,0:16:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Several people I knew were taken away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.85,0:17:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was safe and am still here.\NHow are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.48,0:17:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.19,0:17:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm making it by somehow\Nas a fledgling dentist.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.49,0:17:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,A dentist, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.74,0:17:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You were always good with your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.99,0:17:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I were as good as you\Nat getting ahead in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.91,0:17:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I probably only still have\Nmy current position after the Soviets came
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.21,0:17:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because of my skill\Nat making my way in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.80,0:17:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a lot of fun\Nduring "The Prague Spring."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.43,0:17:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I even went to the West.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.59,0:17:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,When we were kids, we often talked about\Nwhat kind of place the other side was.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.10,0:17:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you find out?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.85,0:17:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I sure did.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.14,0:17:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.81,0:17:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There was nothing.\NThere's nothing neither here nor there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.53,0:17:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This country is broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.49,0:17:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But the countries over there\Naren't any better.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.03,0:17:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.61,0:17:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You said I'm good\Nat getting ahead in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.49,0:17:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I met someone recently\Nwho wants to use those skills of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.62,0:17:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.54,0:18:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy's so amazing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.92,0:18:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that after meeting him, my current status\Nmeans nothing to me anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.63,0:18:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though I believe that this country
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.67,0:18:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and those on the other side have\Nnothing to offer,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.14,0:18:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,he's given me completely new hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.72,0:18:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He's someone who can\Ncreate something completely new.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.64,0:18:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what does this guy create?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.27,0:18:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What does he create? Let's see…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.53,0:18:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It might be something rather frightening.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.78,0:18:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,When I look back on it now,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.20,0:18:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,something inside him\Nmust have started to break then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.79,0:18:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me back my gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.47,0:18:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, you can have your gun back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.97,0:18:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do it, Milan.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.05,0:18:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.26,0:19:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point in stopping me.\NI will kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.98,0:19:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're surrounded by a family now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.61,0:19:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the one who murdered their families.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.32,0:19:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the one\Nwho brought him to this country
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.53,0:19:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,where he killed their families.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.45,0:19:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And… he killed my son too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.41,0:19:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,When they tried to burn down\Nthis neighborhood,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.21,0:19:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,there was someone here\Nwho the Turks still talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.88,0:19:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a Japanese man who rushed around
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.34,0:19:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,caring for the wounded\Nand trying to put out the fires.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.72,0:19:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It was you, wasn't it, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.26,0:19:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.43,0:19:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand very well\Nwhat you're trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.48,0:19:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You and I are the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.36,0:19:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going. It's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.44,0:19:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If I miss this chance,\NI doubt I'll get another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.57,0:19:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Milan!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.20,0:20:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for trying to stop me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.04,0:20:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If I were in your shoes,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.21,0:20:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think I could stop myself either.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.48,0:20:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,ADMISSION TICKET\NMILAN KOLASCH
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.20,0:20:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,-What?\N-Oh my God!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.92,0:20:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is good!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.38,0:20:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. This is delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.46,0:20:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This Japanese oyakodon is good!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.13,0:20:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yes!\N-Indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.05,0:21:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Is your leg all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.10,0:21:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like me to help, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.26,0:21:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Yours is almost ready, Minh.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.60,0:21:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Milan sure is late.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.85,0:21:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he'll be home soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.86,0:21:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It tastes better freshly made,\Nso I'll make Milan's later.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.36,0:21:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? Okay then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.03,0:21:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,…at the Roedelheim Convention Center\Nin Frankfurt,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.58,0:21:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,a man with a handgun opened fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.08,0:21:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The gunman was shot and killed
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.04,0:21:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,by police providing security\Nat the convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.50,0:21:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No other casualties were reported.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.67,0:21:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The center was thrown into panic\Nsince many attendees
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.55,0:21:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,were important people\Nfrom around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.59,0:21:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The gunman's identity and motives\Nare still unknown at this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.60,0:21:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll now show footage\Nof the incident taken by…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.77,0:21:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone loves it! They say it's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.90,0:21:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I sure hope\NMilan gets back soon to have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.32,0:22:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is footage of the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.29,0:22:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That man…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.05,0:22:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the one from the Red Rose Mansion…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.30,0:22:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Keeping secrets from him is a no-no.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.60,0:23:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Subtitle translation by: Brian Athey
